allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params.guy: address The address which will spend the funds.
params.src: address The address which owns the funds.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params.src: The address to query the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

burnfromAdmin(address,uint256).details: Burns a specific amount of tokens from the target address

params.guy: address The address which you want to send tokens from
params.wad: uint256 The amount of token to be burned

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Decrese the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed_[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined) From MonolithDAO Token.sol

params.src: The address which will spend the funds.
params.wad: The amount of tokens to increase the allowance by.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Increase the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed_[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined) From MonolithDAO Token.sol

params.src: The address which will spend the funds.
params.wad: The amount of tokens to increase the allowance by.
